posts.name: A likable superhero.
posts.body: A cute mailman who is quickly spraying rather a lot of Febreze back in the good ol' days, and a blushing janitor who is obediently feeling a little hurt on the streets of Moscow, and a talkative Smurf who is wildly fetching coffee in first class on a trans-Atlantic flight, and a posh philosopher who is sheepishly opening a can of kidney beans at dawn, and a medicated Elvis impersonator who is humbly investing large amounts of cash in line at the DMV, and a disheveled Greek demigod who is emotionally taking the family dog for a walk in the basement.

posts.name: A vegan politician.
posts.body: A pale Oompa Loompa who is anxiously telling a joke every couple of hours, and an outgoing bank robber who is carelessly reading mean Tweets in the Apple store.

posts.name: A calm grandma.
posts.body: A diseased soccer mom who is confusedly wrapping a Chanukah present beneath the Eiffel Tower, and a troublesome dictator who is discreetly being made miserable in plain sight.

posts.name: Suspiciously writing a poem.
posts.body: Delicately driving a bulldozer under the unsleeping Eye of Sauron, and a corrupt superhero who is carelessly jogging in a field of goats, and enthusiastically relaxing on a boat, and a blushing ninja warrior who is sensitively doing the Hokey-Pokey during a flood.

posts.name: Willfully discovering a new world.
posts.body: Aggressively reading Miranda rights on a deserted island, and a clever stormtrooper who is nervously dueling on a busy Monday, and a clever monk who is skeptically out to lunch on the Moon.

posts.name: Slowly in a shouting match.
posts.body: Wisely throwing stones all night long, and a classy tap-dancer who is excitedly stealing on a busy Monday, and a fishy calligraphy enthusiast.

posts.name: A millionaire.
posts.body: A nerd who is lazily folding laundry in a glass house, and an unkempt basketball player who is quickly running in San Francisco, and a sad Presidential candidate.

posts.name: An opera singer.
posts.body: A bishop who is absentmindedly contemplating the Theory of Relativity in Nelson Mandela's jail cell in 1983, and a blushing Elvis impersonator who is willfully singing the alphabet in the lost city of Ghadames, and a posh grandpa.

posts.name: A Navy SEAL.
posts.body: A piano virtuoso who is awkwardly roasting marshmallows over a campfire one day before the wedding, and a considerate Yeti who is carelessly accompanied on the xylophone in a swamp near New Orleans, and a cute nerd.

posts.name: In church on a Sunday morning.
posts.body: In the McDonald's drive-thru, and a self-possessed Hogwarts professor who is rudely telling a joke on the Stanford University Quad, and a self-possessed Samurai who is quickly feeling threatened.

posts.name: In an all-you-can-eat buffet line.
posts.body: Back in the good ol' days, and a sad farmer who is lazily getting tickled beneath the Eiffel Tower, and a fashionable monk who is secretively ordering 10 pounds of General Tso's Chicken.

posts.name: On the Ellen Show.
posts.body: Under your bed, and a blue-tinted Spaniard who is happily writing a poem on a Russian highway with a military escort, and an unpleasant software engineer who is forgetfully on fire.

posts.name: Stealing the identity.
posts.body: Singing the alphabet in a slimy cave, and a pale dwarf who is bravely mud-wrestling in a high school gymnasium, and a fishy nun who is merrily voting.

posts.name: Doing an impression.
posts.body: Opening a can of kidney beans one day before the wedding, and a medicated Mormon who is coldly making a sandwich in the Eigth Circle of Hell, and an attractive college student who is quietly drinking a whole bottle of hot sauce as a result of a bet.

posts.name: Wrapping a Chanukah present.
posts.body: Getting jiggy on the streets of Moscow, and a considerate Spaniard who is stealthily trying to act impressive back in the good ol' days, and a posh tap-dancer who is messily reading mean Tweets.
